events.name: Environmental performance of EV batteries
events.wd_description: The environmental performance of EV batteries is significantly influenced by their chemistry and production location. Transitioning to higher-nickel, lower-cobalt, high-performance automotive lithium nickel manganese cobalt oxide (NMC) lithium-ion batteries (LIBs) from the base NMC111 can reduce GHG emissions but increase SOx emissions.

events.name: GHG emissions
events.wd_description: Transitioning to NMC532, NMC622, and NMC811 cathodes can reduce GHG emissions relative to NMC111.

events.name: SOx emissions
events.wd_description: Transitioning to NMC532, NMC622, and NMC811 cathodes can increase SOx emissions significantly relative to NMC111.

events.name: Projected increase in EV sales and battery manufacturing capacity
events.wd_label: Projected increase in EV sales and battery manufacturing capacity
events.wd_description: The projected increase in EV sales will significantly increase battery manufacturing capacity. Global LIB manufacturing capacity is expected to grow from 40 GWh in 2014 to 2.2 TWh by 2029, with China dominating this capacity.

events.wd_description: Cobalt is primarily recovered as a byproduct from copper and nickel mines, with significant production in the Democratic Republic of Congo and China. The refining stage of cobalt sulfate production is the most energy-intensive.

events.wd_description: The BMS controls the interactions between the LIB and the required load to ensure safe and reliable operation. The study models BMS production in different regions.
